---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About — Aditya Prasad" description="About Aditya Prasad.">
  <div class="about">
    <h1>About</h1>

    <div class="content">
      <p>
        Something happened when I was around five years old. I recognized — not
        as a thought, but as plain fact — that my deepest nature is something
        that doesn't come and go. I've spent the decades since trying to
        understand what that recognition means, and why it's so hard to talk
        about.
      </p>

      <p>
        Around the same age, I taught myself to lucid dream. I had thousands
        of lucid dreams in the following years, offering an additional window
        into the nature of experience.
      </p>

      <p>
        I was also drawn to mathematics early. At eighteen I published a few papers
        in quantum computing with the University of Michigan's quantum circuits
        group (earning me Erdős number 3, through John Hayes). I graduated in
        computer science shortly thereafter and spent eight years as
        a software engineer at Google. While there, I worked as a research
        assistant in psychophysiology at Stanford, coauthoring three papers, and
        taught meditation to colleagues. I kept trying to get these two halves
        of my life to talk to each other.
      </p>

      <p>
        That eventually led me to psychedelics. I've done high-dose psilocybin
        countless times, and many of the ideas I write about here come from
        those experiences. At Google, I pushed for research on psychedelics and
        compassion — briefly collaborating with Johns Hopkins and MAPS —
        because the connection seemed too important to ignore.
      </p>

      <p>
        I write here to think in public: to work through ideas that are still
        forming, and to find others who are asking similar questions. The
        through-line is always the same — how direct investigation of
        experience relates to the formal structures we use to describe it.
      </p>

      <p>
        This site is deliberately simple. No tracking, no analytics, no
        newsletter pop-ups. Just writing.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>

